          <int-org-section id="WFTU.IO.44" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>World Trade Union Congress</heading>
               <p>The Congress, normally held every five years, reviews WFTU's work, endorses reports from the executives, and elects the General Council. The size of the delegations is based on the total membership of national federations. The Congress is also open to partici­pation by non-affiliated organizations. WFTU’s 18th Congress was hosted from Rome, Italy, in May 2022, in a hybrid in-person and virtual format. It was themed `United, we continue! For the satisfaction of our contemporary needs, against imperialist-capitalist barbarity!’.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="WFTU.IO.45" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>General Council</heading>
               <p>The Council normally holds one regular session between Congresses (extraordinary sessions may also be convened), and comprises members and deputies elected by Congress from nominees of national federations. There is one representative from each national trade union centre and Trade Union International, and one representative with consultative status from each affiliated or associated organization.</p>
               <p>The Council receives reports from the Presidential Council, approves the plan and budget and elects officers.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="WFTU.IO.46" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Presidential Council</heading>
               <p>The Council meets regularly and conducts most of the executive work of WFTU. It comprises a President, elected each year from among its members, the General Secretary, 16 Vice-Presidents, and 33 other members.</p>
